	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				After searching for Karg for a month to get a werewolf cloak, I can add some details that most people seem to miss...<BR>
<BR>
Karg's known loot is the Cloak of the Ice Bear (same as the Martar drop) and either a rusty 2 handed sword or a plain 2 hander.  Karg has reportedly not dropped the Gigantic Zweihander in a while, or if he has, nobody admits to it. Yet he is killed for it most every time he spawns.  Too bad Verant's policy is to withold useful information...  : (<BR>
<BR>
Karg is a Quest NPC.  He makes 3 items:<BR>
1) Polar Bear Cloak - requires a polar bear pelt and 5pp<BR>
2) Lupine Claw Gauntlets - requires werewolf claws and 75pp<BR>
3) Werewolf Skin Cloak - requires werewolf pelt and 100pp<BR>
He also despawns after making werewolf items, but not the PBCloaks.<BR>
<BR>
Karg has no set spawn point.  Just like Martar, he may spawn in front of permafrost, the east tower, near the ruins on the river, between the ruins and Megan's, at Megan's, and I think near Starn Bearjumper (barb vendor).<BR>
<BR>
Karg follows EXACTLY the same route as his brother.  So do polar bear cubs, polar bears, and ice goblin whelps.  I believe these to be place holders for Martar (not Karg). Can't figure out what a polar bear cub would be doing in front of permafrost otherwise...<BR>
<BR>
Karg can spawn in as little as 8 hours 40 minutes.  I witnessed this personally. I also have reports of him not spawning for a week...<BR>
<BR>
When I finally did get the chance to complete my quest (no rangers looking for werewolf cloaks), Karg spawned as I was following Martar around the Tundra.  Martar had just crossed the river near the south tower when I received word that Karg had spawned.  Could it be that Martar's trip triggers Karg's spawn?<BR>
<BR>
My advice:  Sit in front of Megan's tower facing the river and you will see Karg, Martar, and any PHs walk by (if they live that long)  If you want him for the werewolf items, offer a reward for Karg's being hailed  (75pp worked for me), and make a few PB cloaks for the lower levels.  They'll thank you for it.<BR>
<BR>
I Hope this info helps.<BR>
Grrumble, 42 Enchanter<BR>
Tholuxe Paells
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
